    "vuln-scanner-template вҠЁ 'findings only contains category vulnerabilities' вҶ’ semantic (requires understanding vulnerability classification)",
    "scan-vulnerabilities вҠЁ 'no duplicates' вҶ’ semantic (requires judging sameness of findings)",
    "classify-severity вҠЁ 'each severity вҲҲ {critical, high, medium, low}' вҶ’ deterministic (enum check)",
    "suggest-fixes вҠЁ 'each fix is concrete code change, not advice' вҶ’ semantic (judgment call)",
    "apply-fixes вҠЁ 'patched-code is syntactically valid' вҶ’ deterministic (parse check)",
    "run-tests вҠЁ 'test-results covers every test' вҶ’ deterministic (compare test list to results)",
    "verify-fixes вҠЁ 'if all-fixed = false then verification identifies which' вҶ’ deterministic (conditional structural check)",
    "generate-report вҠЁ 'report contains all findings' вҶ’ semantic (completeness check requires judgment)"
  ]

  yield awkward-spots вүЎ [
    "AMBIGUOUS: receive-diff вҠЁ 'test-suite is runnable' вҖ” cannot verify runnability without executing. Should be structural: 'test-suite is a non-empty string specifying a test command'.",
    "SEMANTIC-HEAVY: scan-vulnerabilities вҠЁ 'no duplicates' вҖ” deduplication requires semantic judgment about what constitutes the 'same' finding. Could be tightened: 'no two findings share the same file, line-number, and vulnerability type'.",
    "VAGUE: suggest-fixes вҠЁ 'each fix is concrete code change, not advice' вҖ” the boundary between 'code change' and 'advice' is fuzzy. Better: 'each fix contains a replacement code snippet with file path and line range'.",
    "MISSING-ORACLE: generate-report has no oracle checking report format/structure beyond content presence."
  ]

