вҠў redesign
  given В§program вүЎ "(the Cell program from design-cells)"
  given critiqueвҶ’problems вүЎ ["P1...", "P2...", "P3...", "P4...", "P5..."]
  given critiqueвҶ’suggestions вүЎ ["S1...", "S2...", "S3...", "S4...", "S5..."]
  yield В§program'

  вҲҙ Apply suggestions to fix problems in the program...

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):
-- The redesigned program applies all 5 fixes:

  yield В§program' вүЎ "
вҠў receive-diff
  given diff
  given test-suite
  yield diff, test-suite

  вҠЁ diff is a valid unified diff format
  вҠЁ test-suite is a non-empty string

вҠў parse-diff в–ё crystallized
  given receive-diffвҶ’diff
  yield changed-lines[]

  вҠў= changed-lines вҶҗ parse_unified_diff(receive-diffвҶ’diff)

  вҠЁ each changed-line has file-path, line-number, content, change-type
  вҠЁ length(changed-lines) > 0

вҠўвҠў spawn-scanners
  given parse-diffвҶ’changed-lines
  given В§vuln-scanner-template
  yield В§scanner-cells[]
  until length(scanner-cells) = 5
  max 5

  вҲҙ Spawn one scanner cell per vulnerability category:
    injection, xss, auth-bypass, secrets-exposure, buffer-overflow.

  вҠЁ length(scanner-cells) = 5

вҠў vuln-scanner-template
  given changed-lines[]
  given category
  yield findings[]

  вҲҙ Scan В«changed-linesВ» for В«categoryВ» vulnerabilities.
    For each finding, report: file, line, vulnerability type, description,
    and confidence level.

  вҠЁ each finding has file, line, type, description, confidence
  вҠЁ findings only contains В«categoryВ» vulnerabilities

вҠў scan-vulnerabilities
  given scanner-*вҶ’findings
  yield findings[]

  вҲҙ Merge all scanner results into a single findings list.
    Deduplicate by (file, line-number, vulnerability-type) triple.

  вҠЁ no two findings share the same (file, line-number, vulnerability-type) triple
  вҠЁ every scanner's findings are represented

вҠў classify-severity в–ё crystallized
  given scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings
  yield severities[]

  вҠў= severities вҶҗ classify_by_cvss(scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings)

  вҠЁ each severity вҲҲ {critical, high, medium, low}
  вҠЁ length(severities) = length(scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings)

вҠў suggest-fixes
  given scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings
  yield fixes[]

  вҲҙ For each vulnerability in В«scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findingsВ», suggest a
    concrete code fix. Each fix must include replacement code, the target
    file path, and the line range to replace.

  вҠЁ length(fixes) = length(scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings)
  вҠЁ each fix contains replacement-code, file-path, and line-range fields
  вҠЁ each fix references the original finding

вҠў apply-fixes в–ё crystallized
  given suggest-fixesвҶ’fixes
  given receive-diffвҶ’diff
  yield patched-code

  вҠў= patched-code вҶҗ apply_patches(receive-diffвҶ’diff, suggest-fixesвҶ’fixes)

  вҠЁ patched-code incorporates all fixes
  вҠЁ patched-code is syntactically valid

вҠў run-tests
  given apply-fixesвҶ’patched-code
  given receive-diffвҶ’test-suite
  yield test-results, all-pass

  вҲҙ Execute В«receive-diffвҶ’test-suiteВ» against В«apply-fixesвҶ’patched-codeВ».
    Report which tests passed and which failed.

  вҠЁ test-results covers every test in the suite
  вҠЁ all-pass вҲҲ {true, false}

  вҠЁ? on failure:
    retry with В«oracle.failuresВ» appended to prompt
    max 2

вҠў verify-fixes
  given apply-fixesвҶ’patched-code
  given scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings
  given В§vuln-scanner-template
  yield verification[], all-fixed

  вҲҙ Re-scan В«apply-fixesвҶ’patched-codeВ» for each vulnerability in
    В«scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findingsВ», using the same scanner definitions
    from В«В§vuln-scanner-templateВ» for consistency. Confirm each original
    vulnerability is no longer present.

  вҠЁ length(verification) = length(scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings)
  вҠЁ all-fixed вҲҲ {true, false}
  вҠЁ if all-fixed = false then verification identifies which fixes failed

вҠў generate-report
  given scan-vulnerabilitiesвҶ’findings
  given classify-severityвҶ’severities
  given suggest-fixesвҶ’fixes
  given run-testsвҶ’test-results
  given run-testsвҶ’all-pass
  given verify-fixesвҶ’verification
  given verify-fixesвҶ’all-fixed
  yield report

  вҲҙ Compile a structured code review report with sections:
    1. Executive summary: N vulnerabilities found, M fixed, tests status
    2. Findings table: vulnerability, severity, fix, verification status
    3. Test results: pass/fail counts, any regressions
    4. Recommendations: manual review items if any fixes failed

  вҠЁ report has sections: summary, findings-table, test-results, recommendations
  вҠЁ report contains all findings with their severities
  вҠЁ report states test pass/fail status
  вҠЁ report identifies unfixed vulnerabilities if any
"

